  "texts": [
    "Figure 4 depicts the distribution per group and construct, with statistically significant differences marked with * (p <.05) and ** (p <.01).",
    "We observe that participants from the group receiving both adaptive feedback and reflective prompts (G A R) perceived the tool as more useful than the participants from the groups without adaptive feedback (G N A R and G N A N R) and the control group (CG).",
    "Likewise, participants in G A N R (adaptive feedback, no reflective prompts) also reported higher perceived usefulness than participants in G N A R.",
    "It is worth mentioning that the only variant between these two groups was the presence of adaptive feedback.",
    "Moreover, regarding the behavioral intention, both G A R and G A N R (the groups with adaptive feedback) exhibit significantly higher scores than all other groups."
